####COMMANDS#####

1. pwd --> Present Working Directory
2. ls --> list files/dir
3. mkdir [name of dir] -->  Create a directory 
4. cd --> change dir
5. cd .. --> move back
6. rmdir --> Remove DIr
7. cat filename
8. cat >> filename -->
9. rm [filename] -->  remove file
10. wc [filename] --> returns(lines | words | character_count | file_name)
11. touch [filename] --> create a new file
12. ifconfig --> 
13. du --> disk usage
14. df --> disk free
15. ps --> process 
16. kill [pid] --> kill a process
17. man [command] --> man pages
18. ls -l --> long listing format

####FILE PERMISSIONS####
1. Read(4)
2. Write(2)
3. Execute(1)

drwxr-xr-x 2 vzard vzard 4096 Jan  8 11:35 Lab_1

####Users####
1.Owner
2.Group
3.Others

19. chmod [permission] [file_name] -->
20. ls -l > [filename] --> transfer output to file
21. cal -->calander
22. date --> date

#### PIPES ####

ls -l | wc   
[output] | [input]

redirect output of first command as input of second command

{	ls -l > demo	}  
{	wc -l demo		}	same as ls -l | wc


